00:36:05,380 --> 00:36:07,520
what happens to phi one?

982
00:36:08,000 --> 00:36:10,620
It gets changed by amount delta phi one,

983
00:36:10,820 --> 00:36:12,640
which is proportional,

984
00:36:12,940 --> 00:36:13,720
I'll just write equal,

985
00:36:13,920 --> 00:36:16,340
to phi two times epsilon,

986
00:36:16,460 --> 00:36:17,560
times the small angle.

987
00:36:17,960 --> 00:36:19,800
And what about delta phi two?

988
00:36:23,600 --> 00:36:25,280
It's of course proportional to epsilon,

989
00:36:25,620 --> 00:36:25,980
but,

990
00:36:28,000 --> 00:36:29,040
just phi one?

991
00:36:30,440 --> 00:36:31,280
Minus phi one.

992
00:36:35,060 --> 00:36:35,620
Now,

993
00:36:35,620 --> 00:36:37,460
how do you look at a Lagrangian

994
00:36:37,460 --> 00:36:40,480
and decide whether it's invariant under this operation?

995
00:36:41,180 --> 00:36:41,740
Well,

996
00:36:41,740 --> 00:36:42,920
in particular,

997
00:36:43,120 --> 00:36:44,880
if it's written in complex form.

998
00:36:45,040 --> 00:36:46,360
If it's written in complex form,

999
00:36:46,500 --> 00:36:47,720
it's really easy.

1000
00:36:48,340 --> 00:36:49,780
If it contains things,

1001
00:36:49,800 --> 00:36:51,740
like phi star phi in it,

1002
00:36:55,260 --> 00:36:56,460
that's invariant.

1003
00:36:56,760 --> 00:36:58,740
Phi star phi doesn't change

1004
00:36:58,740 --> 00:37:01,280
if you multiply phi by a little phase.

1005
00:37:01,780 --> 00:37:03,680
The same time phi star

1006
00:37:04,620 --> 00:37:06,340
goes to phi star

1007
00:37:06,340 --> 00:37:09,140
times e to the minus i epsilon.

1008
00:37:09,560 --> 00:37:12,060
And so if you multiply phi by phi star,

1009
00:37:12,240 --> 00:37:14,080
the epsilons will just cancel out.

1010
00:37:14,260 --> 00:37:15,460
Phi phi star,

1011
00:37:15,520 --> 00:37:17,180
which is also incidentally the same as

1012
00:37:17,180 --> 00:37:18,880
phi one squared plus phi two squared,

1013
00:37:19,800 --> 00:37:21,940
phi star phi is invariant.

1014
00:37:22,000 --> 00:37:23,420
So if the Lagrangian,

1015
00:37:23,420 --> 00:37:23,960
for example,

1016
00:37:23,960 --> 00:37:25,540
contained phi star phi,

1017
00:37:26,340 --> 00:37:28,740
it could contain phi star phi squared.

